// Atomic-based counter (no scheduler) — minh họa SPEC §16 & ADR-0026 + ADR-0028
//
// Triết không đi kèm bộ lập lịch (no scheduler). Mọi hàm về luồng và Atomic
// đều được quản lý bởi Capability Gate `sys.raw_thread` và `sys.atomic`.
// Chương trình này khai báo yêu cầu quyền và exercise runtime semantics
// trên single-thread VM dev tier per ADR-0028 §9.
//
// **VM dev tier behavior (ADR-0028 §9):** mọi atomic op chạy như plain
// non-atomic read/write. `Ordering` validated typecheck-time, no-op
// runtime. Cross-thread synchronization defers v0.10+ stdlib với real
// OS threading.
//
// **v0.9 scope (ADR-0031 §9 Phương án A — single-call):** Demo exercises
// `let counter = new(0); fetch_add(&+ counter, 1, ...)` end-to-end —
// proves borrow expression syntax + AtomicNew + fetch_add VM dispatch
// + E2420 UseAfterMove enforcement work through the full pipeline.
// Multi-worker pattern requires real Send-boundary refcount-bump
// codegen (ADR-0026 v2 §3.2) which defers v0.10 per ADR-0031 §10.2
// backlog. Until then, attempting `fetch_add(&+ counter, ...)` twice
// fires E2420 — by design.
//
// **VM-ONLY DEMO (interpreter parity gap):** `dao run atomic_counter.tri`
// directly will stack-overflow because the tree-walking interpreter
// doesn't intercept `sys.atomic.*` builtin paths (mirrors the
// outcome_propagate.tri VM-only precedent per CLAUDE.md). To run:
//   $ dao build atomic_counter.tri && dao run atomic_counter.khi
// The in-tree e2e test (`atomic_counter_e2e.rs`) executes via
// in-process VM. Interpreter parity tracked in ADR-0031 §10 backlog.
//
// `Atomic<T>` là built-in type — không cần import. Chỉ `Ordering` enum +
// variants + builtins cần import (per ADR-0028 §8 stdlib module shape).

from sys.atomic import Synchronized, fetch_add, new
from sys.raw_thread import spawn

function spawn_worker(counter: &+ Atomic<Integer>) -> Integer = {
    // Tăng giá trị biến đếm an toàn trên thread. Synchronized = default
    // ordering an toàn cho 95% use case per ADR-0028 §3. Returns the
    // previous (pre-increment) value per ADR-0028 §4.2.
    fetch_add(counter, 1, Synchronized)
}

function main() -> Integer = {
    // Construct Atomic<Integer> initialized to 0.
    let counter = new(0)
    // Single fetch_add — moves &+ counter into spawn_worker per
    // ADR-0031 §4 + ADR-0022 §4.1. v0.9 single-thread VM: returns
    // previous value (0). Multi-worker defers v0.10 (real Send
    // boundary refcount-bump per ADR-0026 v2 §3.2).
    let prev = spawn_worker(&+ counter)
    // counter is now consumed; attempting `&+ counter` again would
    // fire E2420 UseAfterMove per ADR-0025 §5.1 — see .7d enforcement.
    println(f"Atomic counter previous: {prev}")
    prev
}
